Label: 7-methylG-1639
Comment: 7-methylguanosine-1639 refers to the coordinates of the matue 18S rRNA.

Label: pre-rRNA
Comment: A longer precursor transcript that is processed to yield mature rRNAs. This instance of pre-rRNA has no specified length and is used for annotating reactions in which the precursor is not well characterized.

Label: 6-dimethylA-1850,1851
Comment: 7-methylguanosine-1639, 6-dimethyladenosine-1850, and 6-dimethyladenosine-1851 refer to the coordinates of the mature 18S rRNA.
